    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Henckelia corniculata are fever and rheumatism, which are caused by its anti-inflammatory and antipyretic properties. It is also effective in treating respiratory issues such as bronchitis and asthma due to its bronchodilatory and expectorant effects. Furthermore, Henckelia corniculata has been used to alleviate skin conditions like eczema and dermatitis, thanks to its antiseptic and soothing properties. In addition, it has been traditionally used to treat digestive problems like diarrhea and constipation, due to its laxative and astringent properties. The plant's antioxidant and antimicrobial properties also make it useful in treating infections like typhoid and dysentery.",
