    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Henckelia corniculata are anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, antimicrobial, and anti-diabetic. The anti-inflammatory property of Henckelia corniculata is attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic compounds, which have been shown to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes. The antioxidant property of this plant is due to the presence of saponins, which can scavenge free radicals and prevent oxidative stress. The antimicrobial property of Henckelia corniculata is a result of the presence of volatile oils, which have been shown to inhibit the growth of various microorganisms. The anti-diabetic property of this plant is attributed to the presence of phenolic compounds, which have been shown to inhibit the activity of alpha-amylase and alpha-glucosidase enzymes.",
