    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Henckelia corniculata are flavonoids and alkaloids, including mukonine and mukonidine, which have been found to possess antibacterial and antifungal properties due to their ability to inhibit the growth of microorganisms. The flavonoids present in Henckelia corniculata also exhibit antioxidant activity, scavenging free radicals and protecting against oxidative stress. Additionally, the alkaloids have been reported to possess anti-inflammatory properties, reducing inflammation and alleviating symptoms associated with various conditions. Studies have also isolated iridoid glycosides, including corniculatin and corniculin, which have been found to display hepatoprotective effects, protecting the liver from damage. The bioactive compounds present in Henckelia corniculata have been shown to possess these healing properties through various in vitro and in vivo studies.",
